Streams :
----------

If we want to represent a group of objects as a single entity, then we should go for collection.

If we want to process objects from the collection -> Streams
Stream s = c.stream();
java.util.stream package

filter(Predicate)
map(Function)


filter:
--------
input-->10 elements
output--> o to 10 or <=10

map:
------
input-->10 elements
output-->10 elements


stream()
filter()
map()
collect()
count()
forEach()
toArray() --> To convert stream of objects into an array
sorted() --> By default natural sorting order
sorted(Comparator) --> Customized sorting



(s1,s2)->s1.compareTo(s2) ====> Natural sorting order
(s1,s2)->s2.compareTo(s1) ====> Reverse of natural sorting order
(s1,s2)->-s1.compareTo(s2)====> Reverse of natural sorting order













